UPDATE loans SET effectiveReturnDate = #[json:/effectiveReturnDate], lateReturn = (STR_TO_DATE(returnDate, '%Y-%m-%d') <= #[json:/effectiveReturnDate]) WHERE id = #[flowVars.loanId]

UPDATE loans SET studentRegistration=#[json:/studentRegistration], isbn=#[json:/isbn], loanDate=#[json:/loanDate], returnDate=#[json:/returnDate], effectiveReturnDate=#[json:/effectiveReturnDate], lateReturn=#[json:/lateReturn] WHERE id=#[flowVars.loanId]

UPDATE loans SET studentRegistration=(SELECT registration FROM students WHERE id = #[flowVars.studentId]), isbn=#[json:/isbn], loanDate=#[json:/loanDate], returnDate=#[json:/returnDate], effectiveReturnDate=#[json:/effectiveReturnDate], lateReturn=#[lateReturn == true ? 1 : 0] WHERE id=#[flowVars.loanId]
